cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on programming robots using demonstrations. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a novel learning perspective for robots to refine and adapt previously learned skills. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of Gaussian mixture models for learning from demonstrations. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is less likely but still possible as the paper may involve vision-based demonstrations. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also less likely but possible as the paper may involve control of robotic systems.
